unittitle.value: Squatters' Rights Collection: Peter Spagnuolo Papers

p.value: Peter Spagnuolo is a poet and author of   (2001) and   (2005). He was involved in the squatters' rights movement in New York City's East Village in the 1980s which culminated in Tompkins Square Park Police Riot of August 1988.
PLEASE DIRECT FURTHER INQUIRIES TO: tamiment.wagner@nyu.edu
